PoniÅ¼szy wykres przedstawia liczbÄ™ zarejestrowanych Å›mierci na COVID-19 w Irlandii od poczÄ…tku pandemii (marzec 2020). Pochodzi on ze strony https://covid-19.geohive.ie/

Alternatywna wizualizacja

library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)

covid_ie <- read.csv("COVID-19_HPSC_Detailed_Statistics_Profile.csv")

covid_ie %>% 
  select(Date, ConfirmedCovidDeaths) %>% 
  mutate(Date = as.Date(Date)) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(ConfirmedCovidDeaths)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Date, y = ConfirmedCovidDeaths, group = 1)) +
  geom_line(colour = "#DA0059") + 
  geom_point(colour = "#DA0059", size = 0.5) +
  scale_x_date(date_breaks = "3 months") +
  labs(title = "COVID-19 notified deaths",
       subtitle = "Data last Updated: Saturday, 30 October 2021",
       caption = paste("Note:\n 1) The significant IT disruption to HSE",
                       "systems meant that no COVID-19 related\n     deaths",
                       "could be reported during the period 15th May 2021 to",
                       "16th June 2021.\n",
                       "2) From 17th June 2021 onwards, notified COVID-19",
                       "related deaths are reported\n     on a weekly,",
                       "rather than a daily, basis.")) +
  ylab("Confirmed deaths") +
  theme(plot.caption = element_text(hjust = 0),
        plot.title = element_text(size = 16))
